Suppose that a task consists of performing exactly one subtask from among a
collection of disjoint (mutually exclusive) subtasks, say, Subtask 1, Subtask 2,….,
Subtask k. (i.e., the task is performed if either Subtask 1 is performed, or Subtask
2,…, or Subtask k is performed.) Further, suppose that Subtask i can be performed in
ni ways, i = 1,2,…, k. Then, the number of ways in which the task can be performed is
the sum n1+n2+…+nk.

