INTEGER PARTITIONS

Suppose a detergent manufacturer wants to promote her product by giving a gift token
with 100 bars out of the whole stock. The lucky persons among her customers will get
the gift. Some of them may buy more than one bar at a time with the hope of getting
gifts. In how many ways can the 100 gift tokens get distributed? One possible way is
that all the 100 bars with gifts are bought by 100 different customers. We can indicate
this situation by 100 = 1 + 1 + ... + 1. Another possibility is that somebody buys 2
100 times

